#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.141"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.141:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.141:0.2"
msgid "15. Tikaṇḍakīvagga"
msgstr "15. At Tikaṇḍakī"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.141:0.3"
msgid "141. Avajānātisutta"
msgstr "141. Scorn"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.141:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, these five people are found in the world."

msgctxt "an5.141:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

#. VAR: ādheyyamukho → ādiyyamūkho (bj) | ādeyyamukho (s1-3, km) | ādiyamukho (pts1)
#. VAR: momūho hoti → mando hoti momūho (bj)
msgctxt "an5.141:1.3"
msgid ""
"Datvā avajānāti, saṃvāsena avajānāti, ādheyyamukho hoti, lolo hoti, mando "
"momūho hoti."
msgstr ""
"One gives then scorns, one lives together then scorns, one is gullible for "
"gossip, one is impulsive, and one is dull and stupid."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.141:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo datvā avajānāti?"
msgstr "And how does a person give then scorn?"

msgctxt "an5.141:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalassa deti "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a person gives someone robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines "
"and supplies for the sick."

msgctxt "an5.141:2.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an5.141:2.4"
msgid "‘ahaṃ demi;"
msgstr "‘I give;"

msgctxt "an5.141:2.5"
msgid "ayaṃ paṭiggaṇhātī’ti."
msgstr "this one receives.’"

msgctxt "an5.141:2.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ datvā avajānāti."
msgstr "They give to that person, then they scorn them."

msgctxt "an5.141:2.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo datvā avajānāti."
msgstr "That’s how a person gives then scorns."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.165"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.141:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo saṃvāsena avajānāti?"
msgstr "And how does a person live together then scorn?"

msgctxt "an5.141:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, puggalo puggalena saddhiṃ saṃvasati dve vā tīṇi vā vassāni."
msgstr "It’s when a person lives with someone else for two or three years."

msgctxt "an5.141:3.3"
msgid "Tamenaṃ saṃvāsena avajānāti."
msgstr "They live together with that person, then they scorn them."

msgctxt "an5.141:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo saṃvāsena avajānāti."
msgstr "That’s how a person live together then scorns."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.141:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo ādheyyamukho hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a person gullible for gossip?"

#. VAR: adhimuccitā → adhimuccito (s1-3)
msgctxt "an5.141:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo parassa vaṇṇe vā avaṇṇe vā bhāsiyamāne taṃ "
"khippaññeva adhimuccitā hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when they’re very quick to believe what a certain person says in praise "
"or criticism of another."

msgctxt "an5.141:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo ādheyyamukho hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a person is gullible for gossip."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an5.141:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo lolo hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a person impulsive?"

msgctxt "an5.141:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo ittarasaddho hoti ittarabhattī ittarapemo "
"ittarappasādo."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a certain person is fickle in faith, devotion, fondness, and "
"confidence."

msgctxt "an5.141:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo lolo hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a person is impulsive."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an5.141:6.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo mando momūho hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a person dull and stupid?"

msgctxt "an5.141:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo kusalākusale dhamme na jānāti, "
"sāvajjānavajje dhamme na jānāti, hīnappaṇīte dhamme na jānāti, "
"kaṇhasukkasappaṭibhāge dhamme na jānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when they don’t know the difference between qualities that are "
"skillful and unskillful, blameworthy and blameless, inferior and superior, "
"and those on the side of dark and bright."

msgctxt "an5.141:6.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo mando momūho hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a person is dull and stupid."

msgctxt "an5.141:6.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti."
msgstr "These are the five people found in the world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.141:6.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
